rComments: Gerry is by far one of my favorite professors! She's so caring and sweet!

Gerry is a great prof. Super understanding and chill when it comes to due dates. She actually wants to see all her students pass and explains concepts very well. Kind of boring at times but overall great prof. Take her class if you're a bad writer because you're guaranteed to pass with a decent grade.

I didn't go to many classes and still finished with a good grade. It's important to know assignment descriptions and exam previews, but she mostly teaches grammar. She is a tough marker, but provides good feedback. Gerry stays on topic and likes to interact with her students.
Sweetest human on the planet. So compassionate and isnt a hard marker

Gerry is an absolutely amazing prof. She is the most understanding prof I have ever had. She always provides the extra time when needed and is always there to help. She responds to emails very quickly which made it very useful during this pandemic. IF YOU HAVE THE OPTION TO TAKE THIS PROF! TAKE HER!!!

Course material had so much potential yet they managed to make the class SO boring. The TA had a weird superiority complex and was unapproachable. They try to act chill until they start grading :( Also, the quizzes had the more irrelevant prompts. I truly did not learn anything valuable in this class. I would try to skip this prof altogether.
Gerry  the best prof at uOttawa. Caring, provides good feedback and wants you to do well. She is a saint sent from God

Prof Gerry (Arbach, but she prefers Gerry) is the best prof I have had. She cares a lot about her students and she will help you succeed no matter what. She is also very understanding and flexible with deadlines. I wish I could get another class with her. Some people take advantage of her kindness & flexibility. Don't be that person. She is a gem

Gerry is such a sweet prof! She really wants her students to succeed and is extremely flexible with deadlines. She genuinely cares about her students, however, some take advantage of her kindness which really isn't cool. Pay close attention to the feedback she gives on your papers - extremely helpful!

One of my favorite teachers. She gained my respect. She gave me a five week extension on an assignment I lost, an extra four weeks on a research essay, she always gave me the benefit of the doubt, she will give you the extra marks if she can. Always willing to help. Replies to emails fast. Has a VERY good heart.

Gerry is such a cutie. She allowed me to hand in my research essay two weeks late as she did not feel like marking it at the time. Make sure you point with an entire hand in that class or face the consequences....

Gerry is a very kind prof, you can tell she enjoys her job. The content is good and the work load is not bad at all, it was a generally easy class to succeed in. That being said, she was also unbelievably boring. She told the same stories over and over and over and I honestly dreaded going to this class because it was just so dull.

Gerry is an amazing prof! Really cares about her students, and is so understanding. I found that looking through her powerpoints helped me understand exactly what she was looking for. She is sooo sweet and I found my writing got a lot better from taking her class. Would 10/10 take another English class with her again!
Gerry is an amazing prof. she genuinely cares for her students and wants them to succeed. she is the best prof I have ever had, as well she is amazing with extensions and extra help.
great prof, loves her students, doesnt really care about due dates (except final report). lectures didnt really matter, i went occasionally cause she gets to know you if you come to class.
This course wasn't mandatory for me but Im so glad i took it with her. What a great prof to have and she is a very nice lady.
I loved this class. The TA's were amazing. And I learned so much. This has been my favourite class EVER.

She is the most caring & nice prof I've ever had. Actually teaches the material effectively. She memorised everyone's (110) names and faces within the first 3 weeks. Textbook is not mandatory, she might reference a page or two; but honestly, you will never read the books. My HS ENG4U grade was only 72%. I've learnt much from Gerry!

A very sweet lady - like a grandmother. But her Friday 17:30-20:30 lectures were so, so dry. The course itself is rather easy, but it's very heavy in terms of workload. She is very flexible with extensions. Just do things the way she wants - format matters more than content in this class.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'So many papers', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Very sweet woman, not that hard of a class
She is the sweetest prof ever, she cares a lot for her students. she wants you to do well in this course and she will help you in accomplishing that. TAKE THIS PROF IF IT FITS ON YOUR SCHEDULE

She's an incredible woman who cares about her students even to a fault. She continued to accept late work even after the final exam! Very understanding and unintentionally hilarious. She makes it super clear exactly what's expected to succeed. Go to class and hand in the work and cruise your way to an A.

Such a sweet professor. Really cares for the students and wants everyone to do well. You don't need to show up to class since she posts everything online.  A guaranteed as long as you do all the evaluations.
Amazing prof! Just really need to go to the DGDs, not the lecture. Clear expectations.

I had her for my workshop leader. She marks easily and gives us a clear outline on what we should study for the quizzes. Quizzes are 10% each and are easy to get over 90% on each if you just re-read her lecture notes.  If you need more time on an assignment, she usually gives it to you.  Start your final report at least a week in advance.
She's a real kind and good prof.  Don't be afraid to ask her for an extension,  given you don't abuse it.  Material is dry however, although that's not really her fault.
Whatever you start off in the first couple assignments in class; is usually what you end up getting for your final mark.

Geraldine truly cares for her students so don't be afraid of asking for an extension or questions on her assignments which are due every 2 weeks. Her lectures are very repetitive and she just reads of the powerpoint (all on blackboard). The course itself isn't interesting but she marks fairly easily. Quizzes brought my grade up so study for those!
get PDFs for textbooks super boring, refer to slides as an example of how to do the coursework. bring a laptop so you're not bored in class.

As an international student, English courses has been nightmares for me. However, Gerry is very kind to help her students. If you finish your weekly reading on time and start your research essay ahead, you shouldn't have any problems passing it at all. And you will learn something.
She is really good and kind prof. Helps you in every possible way. Lectures are very long and boring but she is very helpful
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Gerry is such a nice prof who truly wants her students to do well. I enjoyed the class a lot more than I had initially expected to. The lectures can be boring but if you do your assignments it's not hard to do well in the class.

Professor Arbach is amazing! The class is prereq for some programs, but it is a bird course. The assignments are simple and easy. Although there are two quizzes, they are not difficult, at all. She is quite the easy marker. Also, there is no midterms/finals. The final report is worth 30%.
The professor only teach the method but not provide enough examples in class and too strict with the homework
Not a good teacher

She is an approachable, kind person. However, be aware that bysigning up for her course you are potentially (depending on your DGD) actually going to be fully marked by a TA. Who does not necessarily know what they are doing. The prof relinquishes all decision power to her TAs, so any bogus requirements and standards can be established by the TA.

If you really have to take English, this is the prof you want to take. The class isn't terribly interesting but she marks very easy. She'll even tell you that in class. Word of caution: this doesn't mean you can completely blow off the lectures. Pay a little attention to what she says and  put some effort into the quizzes and assignments.

She is one of the nicest people I know. Her classes might not be so interesting but she tries her damn hardest to make them. Most of the students aren't that engaged. But once you ask for help and gets to know you. She is your best friend and genuinely cares about you.

She's alright as a professor. She knows what shes talking about but English is such a boring class that I doubt many people were paying attention. The assignments and quizzes were fair and her expectations were clear. Overall, it is a good class even though it's a prereq.

She is the sweetest prof I have had in my life. I like the way she teaches; everything she said in class is very helpful for me because English is my 3rd language. She also offers cookies and chocolates in class :D

She's like a grandma - so nice and repeats everything 5 times. Work and quizzes are easy enough. Going to class is really a waste of time unless you're handing in an assignment. Easy to get a good grade.

While she's a really nice person, her class is the most useless thing ever. This class could be useful, but all of her lectures have the same content but with a different title. Her class is easy, but literally the only reason to go is to get the assignments, and because there's a mandatory attendance rate. Learning definitely doesn't apply here.

Best teacher I have had all year. She knows almost everybody by name (upwards of 150 students), and she is very fun to listen to. She tells you exactly what topics are coming on the quiz's so there is no surprise. Highly recommend attending class. Not many topics to study. Classes never go over 2 hours 30 minutes. Halfway they become ~90 minutes.

Very nice woman. She even brought cookies to our exam. This class was mandatory and really simple. She'd go over everything with us at least twice. Not the best prof if you're looking for a challenge but really nice.
NICEST lady ever! I want to adopt her as my grandma! very easy to get a high mark in her class too!

class might be very borring, but useful. prof is a good one. has very humane attitude towards students. not bad at explaining stuff. marks reasonably. i would definitely like to thank Gerry for making this class as painless as possible!

Gerry is a really nice prof and is very helpful and flexible if you have to miss tests or assignments. The class itself is boring if you even remotely know how to write an essay, for those who don't it's useful. However, don't take it in the three hour chunk, it will be the most boring class you will ever attend.

Good prof overall. Repeats herself, class is pretty boring, but it is english. Lots of grammer, but it did help my writing skills. Very helpful and enthusiastic. Pretty easy A if english is your first language, bit more work for the A+.

Absolutely wonderful! She is passionate about the topic and will explain everything very clearly. If you have any problems, she is willing to help you. Fair marker; everything you learn in her class is useful.
such a boring class. She repeats everything at least 20 times, and you just want to throw something at her. So, the class is useless, and it's a big waste of time.

almost slit my wrists from boredom. tho she is a good teacher, she is waaaay too boring and repetitive.like ZOMG REPETITVE! its annoying how she gives out assignments in class just to force people to come for the class.course in general is unnecessary, i feel, if u have a decent command of english
If you speak english as your first language, switch to a different prof. She goes over commas like you have never heard of them before.
OVERAL SHE IS NOT BAD, BUT SHE OVER EXPLAINS THINGS, AND ALSO SHE TAKES HERSELF TOO SEROUS!

Although class at night, it kept my interest. Grammar quizes very easy and so helpful, easy to bust up your mark! She is such a cute and so smart and gives hints about jobs and such. Tough marker, but seems fair enough. SO AWESOME THAT THE RESEARCH ESSAY IS DUE like three weeks before exams while others have it due the week of exams
Real hot! Ger bear is always a good time. She fires up some tough quizzes unless you study a bit. Learn dangling modifiers and all that.
The class is awful, boring, and very elementary-school esque.   Gerry is a sweetheart though and just wants everyone to succeed.

I cannot stand this class. The degree to which she babies the class is insulting; it feels like a waste of time. She would be a good primary school teacher but is just ridiculous at the university level. It'd be nice if she realized that not all of her students are ESL students and accounted in her lectures. Also, technical writing is TECHNICAL!
She was the most ridiculous prof this school has. Since when do university students do grammar all semester? We're not in the sixth grade. This class was dreadfully boring!!!

Well, she clearly knows her stuff, but I think she'd be better suited teaching the tenth grade. If you already know where the commas go, you'll be extremely bored in this class. She gave me the same grade on every assignment no matter what I did. I wonder if she stopped reading them.

For being an Enlish major I was not very satisfied with this course because one of her T.A did not really understand alot of English compared to some. Also she baby;s the class, but she is clear and repetitive with her instructions.

Wow.  It was an effort just to show up for class every week...Nice prof, but too much hand-holding and repetitiveness....i think grade 12 english was more engaging and challenging than this class.  not to mention the assignments due almost EVERY week....cripes.

Too much work for a non technical Engineering class. I already have to deal with a lot in other Engineering courses. I am not looking to be a novel writer. I just want to be able to write a decent report.
lol....i'm sure that was either DANNY or one of his buddies :P how did i know? who am I? hmmm..... it will always remain a mystery :P
Shes looks EXACTLY like Mrs. Doughtfire...exactly
The class was a breeze but I didn't like Gerry as a prof.  She treats the students like children and there is always something that is due every class.

One of the best teachers I ever had.  Yes, she does tend to go off on tangents, but that makes things more interesting. She really knows her stuff and she's superorganized. Great lady and good marker; her exams are fair and comprehensive.
I found her extremely boring and she had a huge tendency to repreat herself constantly. She treats her students like preschoolers and you do not learn a THING.
Really good teacher. Spends a lot of time on the basics, but know what?  Most people need that in first year!!! Hard marker in a good way - very constructive comments.

Such a nice lady!! she seems easy, but shes a tough marker,&she treats us like JK students.  not always clear, &very repetitive. Shes all about POINTS (L8 pts, deduction pts, grammar pts but never BONUS pts!)she knows grammar in&out, so fait attn!  Very sweet, very helpful, u cant help but like her
Yes, I know what a comma is, thank you. I didn't move from an 86 all term no matter what happened. And, hey, guess what, we're not six years old, so maybe she shouldn't treat us like we are.

harsh marker.. ur mark never goes up.. always in B range... write as simple as possible because she's tough as hell when she marks grammer! She is the most boring prof in first year.. her mouth never stops moving!!!!

Very nice person, but once she decides she wants you to be a b+, that's where you'll stay. Hates university-level writing, and your grade won't change no matter what you do. Little tip: write using nothing but easy anglo-saxon words and use the simplest sentence form possible, or you're doomed.
No Comments

The easiest & most repetitive class ever. If you like gr 8 grammar, and being given the same lecture every class for a month, this is for you. How can it not be easy and clear if the class anticipates you have no working knowledge of the eng language?

This course is a piece of cake, but unfortunately, It's like being taught by a Luddite. This lady has no idea what technology is. She still uses "acetates" and has no website or webnotes. Other than that, she's pretty good.

Two words:  parallel form! Two more:  YOO HOOOOOO!!!  A nice woman, but she goes off on too many unrelated tangents and treats her students like children.  Frustrating as a prof - hard to know what she wants or how she'll grade.
She is a great prof, but tends to be boring as hell. Repeats herself too many times.
Really nice and friendly, though she treats the students as those they are still in kindergarten. She always needs to explain things two or three times, just in case we didn't get it the first time.
Says the word accetate way too much. A good teacher but tries to hard and makes us feel stupid at times. Removes marks because people are doing well; however, isn't that what she wants.
very fun and entertaining. Good prof and answers question clearly.
